bitterness.n.04: the property of having a harsh unpleasant taste
typology.n.01: classification according to general type
upstart.n.01: an arrogant or presumptuous person
permutability.n.01: ability to change sequence
degree.n.06: a unit of temperature on a specified scale
crystal.n.02: a crystalline element used as a component in various electronic devices
work_animal.n.01: an animal trained for and used for heavy labor
beg.v.04: dodge, avoid answering, or take for granted
demist.v.01: free from mist
aftereffect.n.01: any result that follows its cause after an interval
jump.v.04: increase suddenly and significantly
uranyl.n.01: the bivalent radical UO2 which forms salts with acids
fire.v.06: drive out or away by or as if by fire
parade.n.03: a visible display
grey_matter.n.01: greyish nervous tissue containing cell bodies as well as fibers; forms the cerebral cortex consisting of unmyelinated neurons
clinton.n.02: 42nd President of the United States (1946-)
hamstring.v.01: make ineffective or powerless
holly-leaved_cherry.n.01: California evergreen wild plum with spiny leathery leaves and white flowers
warwick.n.01: English statesman; during the War of the Roses he fought first for the house of York and secured the throne for Edward IV and then changed sides to fight for the house of Lancaster and secured the throne for Henry VI (1428-1471)
iconoclast.n.01: a destroyer of images used in religious worship
electrocution.n.01: execution by electricity
accentor.n.01: small sparrow-like songbird of mountainous regions of Eurasia
